## 15.0 Technology Readiness & Validation Pathway

### 15.1 Current Technology Readiness Levels (2026)

| Subsystem | TRL | Status | Path to TRL 9 |
|-----------|-----|--------|---------------|
| **Resource Acquisition** |
| Mechanical excavation | 6 | Terrestrial mining equipment exists; lunar adaptation needed | Analog testing → lunar demo |
| Thermal extraction (sublimation) | 5 | Lab-scale demonstrations; not integrated | Prototype → field test → lunar demo |
| Microwave extraction | 4 | Component testing only | Requires significant development |
| **Processing** |
| Water purification (distillation) | 7 | ISS water recovery heritage | Minor adaptation → qualification |
| PEM electrolysis | 7 | ISS oxygen generation heritage | Scale-up → space qualification |
| **Cryogenics** |
| Hydrogen liquefaction | 6 | Terrestrial systems mature; space adaptation needed | Space-rated design → demonstration |
| LOX production | 8 | Extensive spaceflight heritage (launch vehicles) | Qualification testing only |
| Pulse-tube cryocoolers | 7 | JWST heritage; lunar environment testing needed | Thermal-vac → lunar demo |
| ZBO storage | 6 | Demonstrated in orbit; lunar surface new | Design → test → demo |
| **Power** |
| Fission Surface Power (40 kW) | 5-6 | Kilopower demo 2018 (1 kW); scaling in progress | Prototype → safety approval → lunar demo |
| Solar arrays (vertical) | 7 | ISS heritage; vertical mounting tested | Dust mitigation → lunar demo |
| Regenerative fuel cells | 6-7 | ISS/Space Shuttle heritage; lunar optimization needed | Design → test |
| **Autonomy** |
| Swarm robotics | 5 | Simulation + lab demos; not field-tested | Analog missions → lunar pathfinder |
| AI/ML for operations | 6 | Terrestrial mining automation exists; space adaptation needed | Training → validation |
| Remote operations | 8 | MER/MSL/Perseverance heritage | Adaptation only |
| **Dust Mitigation** |
| Electrodynamic shields | 6 | Lab demos; limited field testing | Lunar environment testing |
| Hermetic seals | 7 | Spaceflight heritage | Lunar thermal cycling tests |

**Assessment:**
- No show-stoppers (all technologies ≥TRL 4)
- Most critical path: FSP (TRL 5 → 9 requires 5+ years)
- High confidence in achieving TRL 9 by 2032 for pilot plant

### 15.2 Critical Technology Development Priorities

**Priority 1 (Essential for Pilot Plant):**
1. **Fission Surface Power:** Accelerate 40 kW development; secure regulatory approvals
2. **Cryogenic System Integration:** Demonstrate complete liquefaction + ZBO in thermal-vac
3. **Autonomous Swarm:** Field demonstrations in analog environments
4. **Dust Mitigation:** Validate EDS and sealing strategies in lunar simulant

**Priority 2